text: Tamara "Tammy" Boyd (born 13 February 1980) is a track and road cyclist from New Zealand. She has been a consistent performer on road and track but she won her first senior title at the 2006 national track championships at Wanganui, winning the scratch race. She represented her nation at the 2005 UCI Road World Championships and 2006 Commonwealth Games. On the track she became national scratch champion in 2006. ==References== ==External links== * profile at Procyclingstats.com Category:1980 births Category:New Zealand female cyclists Category:Living people Category:Cyclists at the 2006 Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games competitors for New Zealand
